title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 01
creator: Thomas D'Arcy McGee
description: Thomas D'Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; Book 1 begins with the earliest modern settlement of Ireland and ends with the 8th century. (Summary by Sibella Denton) M4B audiobook of Complete Series
